<DOC><DOCNO> AP880415-0273 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-15-88 1338EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-TheWeekAhead     04-15 0365</FIRST><SECOND>BC-The Week Ahead,0393</SECOND><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Here are some of the major business events and economic eventsscheduled for the coming week (some dates are tentative):</TEXT><BYLINE>MONDAY, April 18</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The Federal Reserve is to report on the percentageof factory capacity in use during March; release time uncertain.   DETROIT _ Chrysler Corp. and the United Auto Workers union arescheduled to begin negotiations on a new contract.   WASHINGTON _ The Supreme Court issues orders today, possiblyannounces decisions on Tuesday and hears arguments today, Tuesdayand Wednesday.   HOUSTON _ Today is the new deadline for holders of First CityBancorporation of Texas Inc. debt to tender their securities for aloss under a revised federally assisted bailout. The deadline hasbeen extended six times.</TEXT><BYLINE>TUESDAY, April 19</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department is to report the number ofnew homes started in March; due at 8:30 a.m. EDT.   WASHINGTON _ President Reagan is to address the ElectronicIndustries Association dinner.</TEXT><BYLINE>WEDNESDAY, April 20</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The House is scheduled to begin debate on the tradebill.   WASHINGTON _ The Labor Department is to release the ConsumerPrice Index for March; due at 8:30 a.m. EDT.</TEXT><BYLINE>THURSDAY, April 21</BYLINE><TEXT>      WASHINGTON _ The Commerce Department is to report on durablegoods orders for March; due at 8:30 a.m. EDT.   NEW YORK _ Irving Bank Corp., which is fighting a $1.08 billiontakeover bid by Bank of New York Co., holds its annual stockholdersmeeting.   ROLLING MEADOWS, Ill. _ Today is the deadline by which directorsof Staley Continental Inc., the nation's second largest refiner ofcorn sweeteners, plan to announce their response to a $1.33 billionbuyout offer from Tate andamp; Lyle PLC, a major British sugar refinerand distributor.   WASHINGTON _ The Treasury is to report on the government'sbudget deficit for March; release time uncertain.</TEXT><BYLINE>SATURDAY, April 23</BYLINE><TEXT>      VIENNA, Austria _ OPEC's pricing committee is to meet withofficials from non-OPEC oil-producing nations, and perhaps Texas,to discuss ways to bolster oil prices.   WASHINGTON _ Effective today, federal law prohibits smoking onall airline flights of two hours or less.</TEXT></DOC>